  <metadata>
    <title>DSA-3251-1 -- dnsmasq -- security update</title>
    <affected family="unix">
      <platform>Debian GNU/Linux 7.0</platform>
      <platform>Debian GNU/kFreeBSD 7.0</platform>
      <platform>Debian 8</platform>
      <product>dnsmasq</product>
    </affected>
    <reference ref_id="DSA-3251-1" ref_url="http://www.debian.org/security/dsa-3251" source="VENDOR" />
    <reference ref_id="CVE-2015-3294" ref_url="http://cve.mitre.org/cgi-bin/cvename.cgi?name=CVE-2015-3294" source="CVE" />
    <description>Nick Sampanis discovered that dnsmasq, a small caching DNS proxy and DHCP/TFTP server, did not properly check the return value of the setup_reply() function called during a TCP connection, which is used then as a size argument in a function which writes data on the client's connection. A remote attacker could exploit this issue via a specially crafted DNS request to cause dnsmasq to crash, or potentially to obtain sensitive information from process memory.</description>
